t of it because it does carry it's share of benefits and drawbacks.<br><br>After balancing Assassin resists and damage types, I checked the larger resist table to make sure nothing was dramatically altered. All non-Assassin armor resistences were not changes, so target selection remained the same, but Shadowblades benefit from having a new set of targets to choose from based on their specialization choice. Slash and Crush is abundant in every realm for tanks, and Infiltrators and Nightshades are each weak to one of those damage types. Thrust is primarily found in Albion and Hibernia and not in Midgard. Shadowblades do not have an extra benefit because they still face 2 realms that have Thrust, like every other Assassin does to their own weakness.<br><br>The solution in this proposal isn't perfect, but it does the best job so far to even out the playing field between Assassin damage types and resists much better than Mythic ever thunk of. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 8/1/02 2:13:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubilesilhouette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bile Silhouette</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 6:09:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3866.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1.52h Assassin Leather Resist Proposal to Mythic, Hammer</span><hr size=1> This is the most logical, well thought out and best proposal I've seen.<br><br><br><br>I pray they listen and give it a shot.<br><br><br><br><br>I fear they won't.  Though I'll tell braack to come take a peek, I'm sure he has already. <p><B><big><font color="#ffffff">Bile Silhouette</B></big><BR>Pendragon *Legends* Smurf of Death